  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help 300,000 kids realize that Math can be fun</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ganitha Kalika Andolana (GKA) - A Math Movement launched by Akshara Foundation and the Karnataka state Government, aims to improve basic Numeracy skills and facilitate classroom learning of Mathematics in Government primary schools of Karnataka. GKA will help over 300,000 children studying in grades 4 and 5 of 7800 Government-run primary schools attain mathematical fluency. It will also build capacity of over 8000 teachers to enable them to teach Maths creatively inside the classrooms.</narrative>
  </description>
